        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 8:18PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 818 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wildcat Hills State Recreation Area, or 11 miles south of
Scottsbluff, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gering, Bayard, Minatare, Melbeta, McGrew, Wildcat Hills State
Recreation Area, Chimney Rock National Historic Site, Lake Minatare
State Recreation Area, Scottsbluff Airport, Wrights Gap, Moomaw
Corner, and South Bayard Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
the Panhandle of Nebraska.</instruction>
